From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: pai-nix <pai-nix@localhost>
Date: Thu, 11 Jun 2026 00:45:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 26/26] Remove ElevenLabs from the voice runtime (TTS engine
 seam stays)

Upstream issue: (pai-nix — sovereignty policy; no upstream issue.)

Decision (2026-06-11, recorded in glasek/pajplajna.md): the DA voice is
self-hosted; the cloud TTS vendor is removed completely from this
install. This is part 1/3 of the removal — runtime + config. Part 2
(0027) removes the installer's vendor-key step (which includes a LIVE
key-validation egress in engine/detect.ts), part 3 (0028) the
skill-level vendor recipes. DOCUMENTATION/*.md prose mentions stay as
inert residual — they describe upstream, not this install's behavior.

What changes (runtime egress + key plumbing):

  - PULSE/VoiceServer/voice.ts — the vendor TTS implementation inside
    generateSpeech() (api.elevenlabs.io fetch, xi-api-key header,
    eleven_turbo_v2_5 — a model the vendor has meanwhile deprecated
    anyway) is removed; the function stays as the TTS ENGINE SEAM a
    local-engine patch will fill. ElevenLabsVoiceSettings becomes
    VoiceSettings (engine-agnostic prosody shape). API-key resolution
    (config/env), the missing-key warning, and the hardcoded vendor
    fallback voice id (s3TPKV...) are gone. The TTS gate is now
    TTS_ENGINE_CONFIGURED=false; /notify keeps its contract — desktop
    notification still fires, response stays 200 success, no TTS is
    attempted. voiceHealth reports voice_system "none". The 3-tier
    settings resolution, emotional presets, playAudio and the
    pronunciation system all stay — the local engine needs them.

  - hooks/handlers/VoiceNotification.ts — payload type renamed to the
    vendor-neutral VoiceNotificationPayload; voice-events.jsonl now
    logs voice_engine "none".

  - hooks/VoiceCompletion.hook.ts, hooks/lib/identity.ts,
    PULSE/pulse.ts, PULSE/pulse-unified.ts — vendor mentions removed
    from comments.

  - PULSE/PULSE.toml.example — vendor key env example removed.

  - settings.json — two _docs strings de-vendored. The
    daidentity.voices SCHEMA IS UNTOUCHED: the Interview flow keeps
    writing it, and voice ids / prosody values are engine-agnostic
    opaque values a local engine may map or ignore.

  - PAI/USER/Config/PAI_CONFIG.yaml — elevenlabs_key_env removed.

Verified: 33 anchor-checked substitutions (unique-anchor script, 0025
convention); rg -i 'elevenlabs|xi-api' clean across the file set;
voice.ts has zero fetch()/api-key sites left; settings.json still
valid JSON with daidentity.voices schema intact; PAI_CONFIG.yaml still
valid YAML; voice.ts and VoiceNotification.ts transpile (bun build);
synthetic POST /notify with voice_enabled=true returns 200 success and
health reports {voice_system:"none", tts_engine_configured:false}.

Known residual (deliberate): DOCUMENTATION/*.md mentions, PAI-Install
(until 0027), skills (until 0028), Observability finances demo page +
its minified _next chunk — inert text, no egress, no key reads.
